			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">With my first post.. and first idea being naff.. I had another idea.. although with such a well balanced class as a beastlord.. idea's to make the Beastlord class more varied and not to upset the balance is difficult to say the least.
<br />

<br />
Although animal "Taming" did spring into my mind.. - not charms.. or anything like spells.. a Taming skill.. where you find a beast.. be it cat.. wolf.. gator.. griffon.. heh, and you use your tame skill to try and befriend it for a certain length of time.
<br />

<br />
The tame skill could boost a faction modifyer with the beast, and each successful tame attempt would improve the faction, each failed attempt would lower it's faction. Food could also come into play.. certain creatures could like certain foods.. and there would be small or large faction adjustments in the early stages for giving the beast food that it likes. This would be better capping at an early level so that you can't simply give a wolf a whole load of bear steaks to tame it completely.
<br />

<br />
As the faction improves.. it opens up new commands - /pet sit would be one of the first.. then /pet attack then /pet guard etc..
<br />

<br />
Your new tamed creature will have the added risk of turning on you or simply wandering/running off at any moment so you would have to be careful..
<br />

<br />
During the taming process if you wished to log out.. the half tamed creature would go to your inventory and from there you would be able to summon it again to continue the taming process at a later date.. 
<br />

<br />
Once the beast /con's as an Ally you have successfully tamed the creature and you get something akin to a horses bridle - where you can summon your creature anytime you want.. (say with a 30 second casting time)
<br />

<br />
It would replace your warder.. you wouldn't be able to summon your warder as long as you are in the process of taming a creature or have the Tamed creatures "bridle" in your possession. 
<br />

<br />
More powerful creatures would be harder to raise faction to tame them -  and while you use the creature to fight with you.. you would need to keep it's tamed level in check with your taming skill.. so it doesn't turn on you.. or run away etc
<br />

<br />
The creature also wouldn't level with you, so this would give an opportunity for another taming project as you increase in power. Capping the taming skill by level is probably the way to go here if it was to be taken up and implemented.
<br />

<br />
Each race would get a bonus (or be only able to) tame certain creatures:
<br />

<br />
Barb: All creatures of the north: wolves, polar bears, mammoth calves, giant wooly spiders, elder snow griffin, mammoth
<br />

<br />
Vah Shir: All feline mobs: lions, cougars, snow leopards, sabretooths, emerald stalkers, manticore
<br />

<br />
Iksar: All dinosaur/desert insect and scaled: Scorpion, Trakaraptor, rockhopper, greyhopper, wurms
<br />

<br />
Troll: All swamp/insect/nasty creatures: Giant Swamp rat, Mosquito, Snakes, Spiders, Giant Leech, Lamprays, Needlite, Underbulk, Tentacles, and think ... PoD <img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="Wink" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
Ogre: All ursine / gorillas think BIG / bears, owlbears, rhino, cave kodiak, skulking brutes, walrus
<br />

<br />
Each of these creatures would keep it's racial traits but in balance, any creature that procs an effect shouldn't be able to be buffed with the spirit pet procs.. 
<br />

<br />
I think the Beastlord should have some sort of taming ability.. and be the BEST at it.. but sharing some of the ability with rangers, may be the way to go.. can't decide on that.
<br />

<br />
I'm sure this idea has been brought up.. or at least some kind of "befriend animal" idea.. but to make it a skill, rather than caster based would be far better IMO...
<br />

<br />
The creatures you would be able to tame.. would only be an alternative to your spirit warder. and not neccesarily better than the beastlord warder.
<br />

<br />
Let me know what you think..<br />_________________<br /><center>
<br />
