			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Aye it would be complicated.. and possibly something for a LARGE patch or as part of an expansion.
<br />

<br />
The tamed animals would replace the warder. Not really fair to have a BST running around with a menagerie of pets.. heheh..
<br />

<br />
But.. I have had another idea.. this one is a beauty. Tamed animals.. that you can ride as a mount.. which you could also sell to other players.
<br />

<br />
Animal Taming and Mounts:
<br />

<br />
Ok, you tame an animal completely, it becomes your new warder. If it's of a certain type.. big enough to ride around on, you can use tradeskills to upgrade the bridle. I'd say a combination of Tailoring/Smithing/Jewelcraft would be good for this one - and a quest involved depending upon the power of the mount.
<br />

<br />
You set about collecting ingredients, like precious droppable gems, magical ingredients, magical metal ore (which are made into bars that your local enchanter can enchant) and you go into the process of upgrading the bridle. Of course, it would have to be a difficult task to undertake.. and a challenge for the more powerful ridable creatures (mammoth, griffin etc)
<br />

<br />
Once the bridle is successfully combined.. the NO DROP tag is stripped and the creature is bound to the bridle alone.. and not the beastlords taming ability.
<br />

<br />
Certain creatures would have bonus effects for certain classes.. +INT for casters.. +STR for melee etc.. these stats could be placed on the bridle itself.
<br />

<br />
If implemented.. I would like this skill be passed over to other classes in limited form.. such as rangers being able to tame a Unicorn at high level.. but they are limited to taming ridable mounts only.. and not pets that fight with them... if you get my meaning.. yes yes.. i see problems with this too, it would need a lot of ironing out for it to work properly and not throw class "balance" out of the window.. 
<br />

<br />
One of the reasons I'd prefer to see taming rideable mounts passed to other select classes, would be the inflation in beastlord population if this was ever implemented. Could even make a quest spell based for certain magic users for ridable mounts self-only.. The quest would be more like an epic for each class to reflect the difficulty in the beastlord taming ability... all of this is possible.. but balancing it between the classes would be quite a bit of work..
<br />

<br />
For rideable mounts and "epic mounts" - classes (this is just a concept of how it COULD be implemented.. I'm sure people will have their own views on the balance of this):
<br />

<br />
Beastlord: based on skill, the most choice of what to tame. Most unique rideable mounts.
<br />

<br />
Ranger: based on skill, ridable mounts only, limited to a few select ridable mounts and a unique rideable mount for their class(Unicorns for example)
<br />

<br />
Druid: based on epic quest spell... be kinda cool to see a druid riding around on a mist wolf
<br />

<br />
Shaman: based on epic quest spell... a nice bear perhaps?
<br />

<br />
Mage: based on epic quest spell... summon elemental steed.
<br />

<br />
Enchanter: based on epic quest spell... a charm?.. hmm
<br />

<br />
Necro: based on epic quest spell.. summon undead steed.. (i know I know.. global monster file.. )
<br />

<br />
Wizard: based on epic quest spell... not sure what these guys could have, that would be fitting.. maybe a pillar of fire.. heheh
<br />

<br />
Now shadowknights and pallys already get their own summon steed abilities.. and it's base on the coast of the AA to purchase.. could give them an upgrade to it though - pallys get a pegasus.. shadowknights get an evil pegasus.. with dragon wings.. you catch my drift.. <img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="Wink" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
Bards, Monks, Rogues, Warriors - now with this huge and rather scary concept that I have outlined, these guys would be caught in the melee trap.. (which, the recent melee patch and the reasons for it was all about - casters get a boost, and these guys are caught out with nothing) although bards could get a steed song.. but they already have selo's.. hehe
<br />

<br />
I think the ultimate thing for melee, would be an epic quest with a raid tied to the end of it.. fighting a boss mob, which in some way, and tied to the story.. would become a rideable mount for the melee in question.
<br />

<br />
Ok, this additional idea, now that I have wrote it.. seems like an exercise in insanity, not even sure if this will get the creative juices of SoE flowing enough for them to ever implement such a bold, and frankly.. HUGE expansion. The tools to implement the "epic mounts" are already there.. - the bridles to summon mounts.. but the taming concept would need farrrrr more work..
<br />

<br />
By the way.. once a beastlord has a tamed mount.. (that adds abilities, stats etc) he is able to summon his warder again.. or tame another warder/mount
<br />

<br />
Ok, feel free to call me nuts.. <img src="images/smiles/icon_biggrin.gif" alt="Very Happy" border="0" /><br />_________________<br /><center>
<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=933999" target="_blank">
