				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I like the idea of animal taming. I don't think it should be based on factions and/or change any factions either. We are already friendly to animals with the exeption of beasts. They should make all anima and beast types friendly to us Beastlords (see the name?) and allow us to tame such animals/beast to aid us in battle for a period of time, think of it as a DPS burst. Not a tamed animal/beast to replace our warder, nothing should replace our warder; my warder is my friend and he wouldn't feel happy if I replaced him with someone else, how would you feel if your warder decided he/she is moving on to someone else? <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="Smile" border="0" />    Just give us tame animal/beast and place more of these in every zone and have them wander. Tame them to aid you in battle, say for 30 secs, and flag that animal/beast untameable for 5mins. There shouldn't be a reason to penalize us for having a damage burst for 30 secs (Ranger True Shot? Pallies Slay Undead? etc), and the spell Track Animal can become useful.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
